<DOC><DOCNO> DOE2-58-0082 </DOCNO><TEXT>Two resource documents have been developed to provide technical assistanceto states and compact regions in selecting and characterizing sites fordisposal of low-level radioactive wastes (LLW). The Site Selection Handbookprovides basic information on the components of a comprehensive siteselection program. It also serves as the basis for a two-day workshopon site selection. The Site Characterization Handbook is a referencedocument for developing and managing a comprehensive site characterizationprogram which will support a license application for a LLW disposal facility.</TEXT></DOC>